      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's crazy how much people just ignore this. like, if you look at the specific buildings that anchor these \"sigils\"—mostly old banks, central intelligence hubs, or massive corporate towers—it's like they aren't just offices, they're nodes in the circuit. and when u look at the timing of when these lines intersect, it's almost like the city is built to \"activate\" at certain times. if this is real, then the geometry isn't just a map, it's a control mechanism. do u see any other major cities that follow this same kind of geometric logic? i feel like if i find one more, it's definitely not just a coincidence anymore.",
